    "comment": "Rationale: Using electron microscopy of mouse suprachiasmatic nucleus (SCN) sections, the authors found that 5HT1b receptors were localized at the plasma membrane of axon terminals (presynaptic) of retinohypothalamic tract neurons that provide input to SCN.\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\n- \"Immunoreactivity was never seen within the region of synaptic specializations\". Experimental description: Mice (C57BL/6J; male; The Jackson Laboratory, Bar Harbor, ME)\nbetween 6 and 12 weeks of age were used for light microscopic analysis\nof RHT and 5-HT afferents in the SCN and for electron microscopic\nimmunocytochemical analysis of 5-HT1B receptors in the SCN.",
